The correct way to make text bold in CSS is by using the "font-weight" property and setting it to "bold". 

Example:

```
p {
  font-weight: bold;
}
``` 

This will make all paragraph text within the selected element to appear in bold font.

The property used to change the left margin of an element is `margin-left`. 

Example:

```
div {
  margin-left: 20px;
}
```

This will add a left margin of 20 pixels to the `div` element.

The property used to change the font of an element is `font-family`.

Example:

```
p {
  font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
}
```

This will set the font family of all `p` elements in the page to `Arial`, and if it's not available, the font will fall back to any other sans-serif font available in the user's device.

How do you make a list that lists its items with squares?
